* DA-60: Global Patient ID (GPID): Implement a global_patients table to link a single human to multiple clinic_patients records. This allows a patient in chain clinics to use their wallet in Clinic A even if they were registered in Clinic B. (p. 4)
* DA-61: Conflict-Aware Merge Logic: Add a patient_merge_log and a service to merge two profiles. It must reassign all invoices, appointments, and photos from the source to the target ID without losing data. (pp. 1-2)
* DA-62: Consent Snapshotting: In the patient_consents table, add a form_snapshot_json column. Store the exact text the patient signed at that moment, not just a link to a template.
* DA-63: Resource Capacity Pooling: Instead of tagging "Room 101," allow clinics to define "Resource Pools" (e.g., "5 Laser Beds"). The scheduler should only warn if the 6th concurrent laser session is booked. (p. 3)
* DA-64: Machine-Service Mapping: Link specific services to resource_types (e.g., "Full Body Laser" requires "Laser Machine"). Show a yellow warning if a machine is likely overbooked. (p. 3)
* DA-65: Status-Triggered Flow: Add checked_in_at, consultation_start_at, and treatment_complete_at to the appointment table to calculate "Patient Wait Time" analytics
DA-70: Protocol-Driven Follow-ups: Create a treatment_protocols table. When a "PRP Session" is marked complete, the system must auto-suggest a follow-up appointment in exactly 30 days. (pp. 5-6)
* DA-72: Inventory Transit Lock: Implement a 2-step transfer: In-Transit (Stock leaves Clinic A) and Received (Stock enters Clinic B). Prevent stock from "vanishing" during inter-branch transfers. 

* DA-73: Marketing Attribution: Add utm_source, utm_medium, and lead_source to the patients table to track which Instagram or Google ad actually generated the revenue. (pp. 7-8)
* DA-74: Referral Reward Ledger: Add a patient_referrals table. If Patient A refers Patient B, auto-credit Patient A’s wallet only after Patient B pays their first invoice. (p. 8) 

6. System Health & Scaling (P1) 
* DA-75: Webhook Reliability: Add a webhook_logs table with a retry_count. If the WhatsApp or Razorpay notification fails, the system must retry 3 times before alerting the "God Mode" dashboard. (pp. 9-10)
* DA-76: JSONB Metadata Flex-Fields: Add a metadata JSONB column to patients, appointments, and inventory_products to allow clinics to add custom fields (like "Skin Type") without database migrations. (p. 10) 

